cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.CY 

This paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category as it deals with recommending news articles based on browsing behavior. It may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it introduces a new class of news recommendation systems. Additionally, it could be classified under Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) as it involves analyzing the content of news articles. The sub-categories of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) and Computers and Society (cs.CY) are also possible as the paper discusses the challenges of news recommendation and the impact it has on users.
